Persona Companion App - Feature Roadmap
This document outlines planned features and expansions for the Persona Companion App to make it the ultimate, all-in-one reference tool for the Persona series.
 Phase 1: Data Expansion
1. Item Compendium & Weapons Database
[ ] Create Item JSONs: Map out Weapons, Protectors, Accessories, Consumables, Skill Cards, and Materials.
[ ] Itemization / Execution: Add data for P5R Electric Chair/Fusion Alarms and P3 Weapon Fusion (which Personas give which items).
[ ] Reverse-Lookup Engine: Link the Item database to the Enemy database. (e.g., Viewing "Onyx" shows "Dropped by: Sky Balance" and links to the enemy profile).
[ ] UI Implementation: Create an ItemCompendiumScreen utilizing the existing filter chips (Filter by Type, Source, Game).
2. Side-Quest & Request Tracker
[ ] P3/P3R Velvet Room Requests: Track Elizabeth/Theodore request numbers, required items, deadlines, and rewards.
[ ] P4G Quests: Track the Fox (Hermit) multi-step fetch quests and Inaba NPC requests.
[ ] P5R Mementos Requests: Track Mishima's requests, target names, unlock conditions, Mementos Path/Floor, and link the target directly to their EnemyDetailScreen profile.
3. Social Link / Confidant Benefits
[ ] Update Social Link JSONs: Inject an ability or benefit object into the rank nodes.
"Rank 7": {
  "Ability": {
    "Name": "Insta-Kill",
    "Description": "Chance to instantly win a battle..."
  },
  "Dialogues": [ ... ]
}


[ ] Rank 10 Ultimate Personas: Add a benefit to every Rank 10 indicating which Ultimate Persona is unlocked for fusion.
[ ] UI Implementation: Add a distinct, themed "Benefit Card" (e.g., Red for P5, Blue for P3) above the dialogue choices on the SocialLinkDetailScreen.
4. Shadow Negotiation Guide (P5/P5R)
[ ] Update Enemy JSONs: Add a personality field (Upbeat, Timid, Irritable, Gloomy) to Persona 5 enemies.
[ ] UI Implementation: Add a Negotiation Cheat Sheet to the EnemyDetailScreen indicating which dialogue tones the shadow Likes, Dislikes, and is Indifferent to.
Phase 2: Advanced Tools & Calculators
1. Forward Fusion Calculator
[ ] Logic Update: Expand FusionCalculator.kt to allow "Forward Fusion".
[ ] UI Implementation: Allow users to select two Personas from a list (representing their current inventory) to calculate the resulting Persona.
2. Standalone Skill Compendium
[ ] Create Skill Database: Extract all skills into a standalone, searchable list.
[ ] Skill Details: Show HP/SP cost, effect, and a list of all Personas that learn the skill naturally or drop it as a Skill Card.
3. Custom Persona "Build" Planner
[ ] Build Creator: Allow users to select a Persona and assign 8 specific skills from the Skill Compendium.
[ ] Save Functionality: Save these custom builds to local storage (SharedPreferences/Room) under a new "My Roster" tab.
4. Party / Elemental Loadout Builder
[ ] Roster Dashboard: Allow users to add up to 12 Personas to an active roster.
[ ] Weakness Calculator: Calculate and display the combined elemental resistances and weaknesses of the entire roster to help players balance their team.
Phase 3: Quality of Life & Immersion
1. Daily Schedule & Calendar Helper
[ ] Availability Tracker: Filter S-Links by day of the week, time of day (Day/Night), and weather (e.g., Rainy days in P4G).
[ ] Missables Checklist: Create a tracker for time-sensitive events (Tartarus missing persons deadlines, specific book availability dates, P5R third-semester unlock deadlines).
[ ] Exam Quick-Reference: Create standalone UI cards that pop up with exam answers right before the in-game midterm/final dates.
2. Dynamic UI Theming & Audio
[ ] Game-Specific Themes: Dynamically shift the app's MaterialTheme colors based on the active game (e.g., smooth transition to Deep Red for P5, Melancholic Blue for P3, Bright Yellow for P4).
[ ] Audio Flourishes: Add optional UI sound effects matching the iconic menu sounds (swish/clicks) of the respective games to increase immersion.
